  "prompt": "Has anyone ever tried Nikola Tesla's cosmic energy collector? What were the results?",
  "response": "Nikola Tesla's concept of a cosmic energy collector, sometimes referred to in connection with his ideas about harnessing \"free energy\" from the environment, has not been successfully realized in a scientifically validated manner. Tesla experimented with various forms of wireless energy transmission and believed in the possibility of extracting energy from the Earth's atmosphere, but the practical implementation of these ideas has proven difficult.\n\nThere have been various interpretations and attempts based on Tesla's concepts by inventors and enthusiasts over the years, but many of these claims often lack rigorous scientific backing and replicability. Tesla's original designs, such as the Wardenclyffe Tower, were primarily aimed at transmitting electrical energy wirelessly rather than collecting cosmic energy in the way that some people today interpret his vision.\n\nThe scientific community remains skeptical of the feasibility of free energy devices. While Tesla's work was groundbreaking in many ways, attempts to develop a working cosmic energy collector have not yielded successful or credible results that align with modern scientific understanding.",
